questions.question:
Let Q = ({q_0, q_1}, {a, b}, {a, b, 1}, delta, q_0, 1, phi) be a pushdown automaton accepting by empty stack for the language which is the set of all nonempty even palindromes over the set {a, b}. Below is an incomplete specification of the transitions delta. Complete the specification. The top of the stack is assumed to be at the right end of the string representing the stack contents.

1. delta(q_0, a, 1) = {(q_0, a1)}
2. delta(q_0, b, 1) = {(q_0, b1)}
3. delta(q_0, a, a) = {(q_0, aa)}
4. delta(q_0, b, b) = {(q_0, bb)}
5. delta(q_0, a, b) = {(q_0, ab)}
6. delta(q_0, b, a) = {(q_0, ba)}
7. delta(q_1, a, a) = {(q_1, epsilon)}
8. delta(q_1, b, b) = {(q_1, epsilon)}
9. delta(q_1, epsilon, 1) = {(q_1, epsilon)}
10. delta(q_0, a, b) = {(q_1, ?)}
11. delta(q_0, _, _) = {(q_1, ?)}

Which transitions complete the specification?
A. delta(q_0, a, a) = {(q_1, epsilon)}, delta(q_0, b, b) = {(q_1, epsilon)}
B. delta(q_0, a, a) = {(q_1, a)}, delta(q_0, b, b) = {(q_1, b)}
C. delta(q_0, a, a) = {(q_1, epsilon)}, delta(q_0, b, b) = {(q_1, epsilon)}, delta(q_0, epsilon, 1) = {(q_1, epsilon)}
D. delta(q_0, a, a) = {(q_1, aa)}, delta(q_0, b, b) = {(q_1, bb)}

Which of the following languages over {a, b, c} is accepted by a deterministic pushdown automaton?
A. {a^n b^n c^n | n >= 0}
B. {ww | w in {a, b}*}
C. {ww^R | w in {a, b}*}
D. {w | w is a palindrome over {a, b, c}}

Note: w^R is the string obtained by reversing w.

Let M = ({q_0, q_1}, {a, b}, {a, b, 1}, delta, q_0, 1, phi) be a Pushdown automaton where delta is given by:
delta(q_0, a, 1) = {(q_0, a1)}
delta(q_0, b, 1) = {(q_0, b1)}
delta(q_0, a, a) = {(q_0, aa)}
delta(q_0, b, b) = {(q_0, bb)}
delta(q_0, a, b) = {(q_0, ab)}
delta(q_0, b, a) = {(q_0, ba)}
delta(q_0, a, a) = {(q_1, epsilon)}
delta(q_0, b, b) = {(q_1, epsilon)}
delta(q_1, a, a) = {(q_1, epsilon)}
delta(q_1, b, b) = {(q_1, epsilon)}
delta(q_1, epsilon, 1) = {(q_1, epsilon)}

a. What is the language accepted by this PDA by empty stack?
b. Describe informally the working of the PDA.
